autoChirp.tweetCreation

Class Tweet

  • java.lang.Object
    • autoChirp.tweetCreation.Tweet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Tweet>

    public class Tweet
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Tweet>
    represents a single tweet consisting of content, tweetDate, imageUrl (optional), and geo-locations (optional). If read from DB, also consisting of tweetID, groupID, groupName and the status-attributes scheduled and tweeted
    Author:
    Alena Geduldig

        public Tweet(java.lang.String tweetDate,
             java.lang.String content,
             int tweetID,
             int groupID,
             boolean scheduled,
             boolean tweeted,
             int userID,
             java.lang.String imageUrl,
             float longitude,
             float latitude)
        Constructor for tweets read from the database. In contrast to new tweets, tweets read from DB already have a tweetID, groupID, userID and status-attributes
        Parameters:
        tweetDate - scheduling date of the tweet
        content - the tweets content
        tweetID - db-key
        groupID - db-group-assignment key
        scheduled - tweet is already scheduled and will be tweeted
        tweeted - tweet has already been tweeted
        userID - db-user-assignment key
        imageUrl - link to an image
        longitude - longitude of geo-location
        latitude - latitude of geo-location
